{"bill":{"bill_id":1651570,"change_hash":"c32fb6694ec42d38af60459bbf300e2e","session_id":1988,"session":{"session_id":1988,"state_id":46,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2023,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023 Regular Session","session_name":"2023 Regular Session"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/VA\/bill\/SB1140\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/lis.virginia.gov\/cgi-bin\/legp604.exe?231+sum+SB1140","completed":0,"status":2,"status_date":"2023-02-02","progress":[{"date":"2023-01-10","event":1},{"date":"2023-01-10","event":9},{"date":"2023-01-27","event":10},{"date":"2023-01-31","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-02","event":2},{"date":"2023-02-10","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-13","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-16","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-16","event":9}],"state":"VA","state_id":46,"bill_number":"SB1140","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"S","body_id":8,"current_body":"H","current_body_id":7,"title":"DARS; training, powers, and duties of guardian.","description":"Department for Aging and Rehabilitative Services; training; powers and duties of guardian; annual reports by guardians; information required. Directs the Department for Aging and Rehabilitative Services to develop and provide training for court-appointed guardians by July 1, 2024. The bill requires an appointed guardian, except a guardian who is licensed to practice law in the Commonwealth, and any staff employed by such guardian to perform guardianship duties to complete the initial training developed by the Department within four months of the date of the initial court order of appointment and guardians and such staff appointed prior to July 1, 2024, to complete such training by January 1, 2026. The bill further requires a guardian to include in his annual report to the local department of social services a statement as to whether such training has been completed.  Department for Aging and Rehabilitative Services; training; powers and duties of guardian; annual reports by guardians; information required. Directs the Department for Aging and Rehabilitative Services to develop and provide training for court-appointed guardians by July 1, 2024. The bill requires an appointed guardian, except a guardian who is licensed to practice law in the Commonwealth, and any staff employed by such guardian to perform guardianship duties to complete the initial training developed by the Department within four months of the date of the initial court order of appointment and guardians and such staff appointed prior to July 1, 2024, to complete such training by January 1, 2026. The bill further requires a guardian to include in his annual report to the local department of social services a statement as to whether such training has been completed.","pending_committee_id":0,"committee":[],"referrals":[{"date":"2023-01-10","committee_id":4165,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"name":"Judiciary"},{"date":"2023-01-18","committee_id":168,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"name":"Rehabilitation and Social Services"},{"date":"2023-01-27","committee_id":164,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"name":"Finance and Appropriations"},{"date":"2023-02-10","committee_id":150,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Courts of Justice"},{"date":"2023-02-13","committee_id":154,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Health, Welfare and Institutions"},{"date":"2023-02-16","committee_id":147,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Appropriations"}],"history":[{"date":"2023-01-10","action":"Prefiled and ordered printed; offered 01\/11\/23 23102600D","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-10","action":"Referred to Committee on the Judiciary","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-18","action":"Rereferred from Judiciary (8-Y 0-N)","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-18","action":"Rereferred to Rehabilitation and Social Services","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-27","action":"Re